<subpara id="RM000000XOK019X_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00002TD00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The Air-Fuel Ratio (A/F) sensor varies its output voltage in proportion to the air-fuel ratio. If the A/F sensor impedance (alternating current resistance) or output voltage deviates greatly from the standard range, the ECM determines that there is an open or short malfunction in the A/F sensor circuit.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
